trend_summary: Across the five time-steps, a predominantly agricultural landscape shows slight urban growth along the central east-west corridor. Field boundaries become larger and more regular, while forest patches shift marginally southward. Built-up footprints expand modestly near the main road, yet open land still dominates, keeping overall character rural and low-density.
